An allied health professional who administers radiation in various forms using varying methods of administration.
A registered or licensed practical nurse who provides education to other clinicians and/or patients.

Nurse Practitioners (NPs), are registered nurses with additional education and experience who are able to order and interpret diagnostic tests, communicate diagnoses, prescribe pharmaceuticals and perform specific procedures.

designation.value: Fellow of American Academy of Osteopathy (occupation)
Fellow of American Academy of Osteopathy
FAAO - Fellow of American Academy of Osteopathy

This earned post-doctoral fellowship is conferred by the American Academy of Osteopathy. Those who earn the FAAO must demonstrate their commitment to osteopathic principles and practice through teaching, writing, and service, performed at the highest level of professional and ethical standards.
Unlicensed individual who may have training or certification and performs routine care activities for a patent in the home and may assist with activities of daily living.
A person who performs routine tasks and household duties for a patient in their home.
A person who teaches in schools on the subject of promotion of health awareness and prevention of disease or injury.
Clinician involved in a research study who is responsible for medical care of a subject or subjects in the study.
A non-medical person who stays with and assists a woman before, during, or after childbirth.
A person who provides support and guidance to an individual or a group of people such as a family or community during a crisis.
Person qualified and licensed to practice in fields including nutrition, food science and public health.
Public health professional who investigates patterns and causes of disease and injury in humans.

A person who undertakes a collaborative process of assessment, planning, facilitation, care coordination, evaluation, and advocacy for options and services to meet individual and family. comprehensive health needs.
A physician who has the authority and assumes the responsibility for patient discharge from a healthcare facility.
A person who has the responsibility of communicating and coordinating healthcare interventions for individuals in populations with a specific condition.
Individual who provides personal guidance to patients as they move through the health care system. Patient navigators may have professional medical, legal, financial, or administrative experience.
Physician whose practice is limited to care of hospitalized patients.
A healthcare professional that possesses expertise in a clinical domain and provides advice on the diagnosis and management of individuals with conditions related to that domain.
